sentences: Amazing how he relishes pressure situations and brings out the best.
Anyway, India have registered their first victory of the tournament and the dressing room will be a little more relaxed now.
So that's it from this game then.
Hope you enjoyed the coverage.
The action continues tomorrow and it's a double-header.
First up, it's South Africa v Afghanistan in Mumbai and then Sri Lanka v West Indies in Bangalore.
Looking forward to your company then.
Good night, goodbye!It was pretty gloomy out there in the evening and dark clouds threatened to play spoilsport.
However, the rain gods were kind enough to allow us an 18-over contest and India picked up a much needed win.
6 matches, 6 inninngs, 3 not-outs,  .
runs, a best of 78*, and average of  .
6 and a strike-rate of  .
This is Virat Kohli's record against Pakistan in T20Is.
Now hang on, read this.
3 matches, 3 not-outs,  .
runs.
This is Kohli's record against Pakistan in World T20s.Dhoni: "I didn't expect it to spin so much.
The spinners got plenty of help out there.
It got slightly better in the second half and they had only one spinner.
I think we can still do better (playing against spin).
There are areas where we can still improve.
It is important that you when you win games you address all those areas.
You won't get a second chance in the knockout stages.
The third seamer can give you a bit of help if there is dew around, but if I knew that there was so much turn on offer, then I don't have a problem playing an extra spinner.
In this format every team is a good team.
We want to compete.
We want to be here for the final, but as of now we want to take one game at a time.
"Afridi: "First of all, I want to congratulate Dhoni and his team for playing well.
I did not expect the pitch to spin so much, but no excuse.
I think we didn't score enough runs.
We were short by  .
5 runs.
Their spinners bowled well.
I think we didn't bowl in the right areas and I didn't bowl well.
Virat Kohli played an awesome innings.
I would have picked another spinner for this pitch.
India play very well under pressure.
Their batsmen play well under pressure and our batsmen have to learn from them in that aspect.
We are playing Australia and New Zealand next, so we've got to play very well.
This game is done, we need to quickly focus on the next game.
"Kohli: "It was a challenging wicket out there.
You need new challenges every innings that you play.
I was disappointed that I got out for about 25 in the last game.
I knew if I had scored  .
5 we could have won.
That really hurt because we don't bat like that at home.
Today it was all about keeping calm and luckily I got a great partnership with Yuvraj.
49 odd I scored in Dhaka against Pakistan was probably one of my better knocks.
I think the seamers bowling cutters was a little difficult.
You need to watch the ball to play it late to dab it down to third man.
Yuvraj came out, weathered the storm and smacked a few.
It's great for him that he came out in a pressure situation.
He's feeling confident.
I think a score on the board always helps me calculate better (talking about his success in run-chases).
"Virat Kohli is the Man of the MatchAfridi took the ball.
Then Malik.
This should have been the phase where Pakistan win it.
And then Kohli took charge.
What a player.
He ensured that the strike kept rotating and put on a 61-run partnership with an ever-gaining-in-confidence Yuvi that nearly sealed it.
Just the way he carried himself.
His presence.
Looked a class apart.
Admittedly, Pakistan's spin duo of Malik and Afridi greatly underwhelmed and looked nowhere near threatening on a spin haven.
That's where they lost it.India knew they had a game on their hands chasing a decent looking  .
on a carnivorous turner.
But what hit them wasn't turn.
Rohit fell early to Amir in trying to loft him over the top.
Then Sami rattled in and struck twice in one over to leave Eden Gardens in trauma and India tottering at  .
Pakistan were right on top.
They hadn't even introduced spin and had India at their mercy.
In walked Yuvraj Singh.
A man who has taken a lot of flak, some would say he has been made the scapegoat whenever they lose.
Imagine the pressure.Another opportunity for Dhoni to finish a game and he doesn't miss out.
Kohli punches the air in delight, before the players exchange handshakes.
Much needed win for India to get their  .
World T20 campaign back on track.
They were under a lot of pressure on the team after losing the first game to New Zealand and they have responded well.
How well is Kohli under pressure and how well he handles pressure!
Gee, he's such a player and it was great to see him take responsibility and perform so well.
Irfan to Dhoni, 1 run, it's a clean sheet ( . )
for India over Pakistan in World Cup contests.
Batting maestro Sachin Tendulkar waves the Indian flag in joy in the stands.
Meanwhile, Kohli points his bat towards the sky.
Shortish delivery on the off stump, Dhoni easily pulls it through mid-wicket and jogs across .
Irfan to Dhoni, SIX, in the slot and baaaaaang.
Dhoni muscles one down the ground and sends it towards the sightscreen.
Slower delivery outside off stump, Dhoni goes over mid-on.
The Indian dug-out is delightedJust 7 to get now for India .
Irfan to Kohli, 1 run, shortish slower delivery on the stumps, Kohli works it to square leg .
Irfan to Kohli, FOUR, Kohli wants to celebrate early.
He's batting brilliantly out there.
Short and wide outside off stump, Kohli cuts off the back foot, once it beat backward point, the ball rocketed to the fence.
The crowd is absolutely loving this .
Irfan to Dhoni, 1 run, slower delivery on the off stump, Dhoni steps out and guides it to third manMohammad Irfan [ .
is back into the attack .
Afridi to Kohli, no run, Kohli tries to work it on the on-side, gets a soft leading edge that rolls to cover .
Afridi to Dhoni, 1 run, down the leg-side, glanced away to backward square leg .
Afridi to Dhoni, no run, how did that miss the stumps?
Dhoni was on the front foot to drive, got an inside edge onto pad, Afridi kept appealing for LBW, and the ball almost disturbed the stumps as well .
Afridi to Kohli, 1 run, tell him that he's playing against Pakistan in T20Is and he'll score runs at will.
Flighted delivery outside off stump, Kohli drives to long-off and brings his up fifty.
No great celebration from Kohli, just lifts his bat to the crowd and the dressing room .
Afridi to Kohli, FOUR, and again!
He's played that inside-out cover drive so well today.
Once again those wrists come ino play.
Too full from Afridi, Kohli nails the drive after leaning forward, the fielder in the deep had no chance .
Afridi to Dhoni, 1 run, flighted delivery from Afridi, Dhoni drives it to long-offIt's 20 needed off 24 now.
The Indian captain looks relaxed out there .
Amir to Kohli, FOUR, wow!
Just wow!
What timing from Kohli.
Full and in the slot, Kohli leans forward and places the drive through cover, he didn't try to hit it hard, just timed it so sweetly through extra-cover .
Amir to Kohli, no run, ah beaten!
Good length delivery wide outside off stump, pokes and plays a long way away from the body, he does that every now and then and luckily he didn't edge this .
Amir to Dhoni, 1 run, round the wicket, short of length delivery on the stumps, Dhoni works it through mid-wicket .
Amir to Kohli, 1 run, he's so good in guiding the ball to third man and Pakistan will have to stop giving time and width outside off stump to Kohli .
Amir to Dhoni, 1 run, slower delivery just outside off stump, Dhoni tries to punch, goes off the inner half of the bat to long-on .
Amir to Kohli, 1 run, slower delivery outside off stump, Kohli dabs it down to third manMohammad Amir [ .
-1] is back into the attackJust 28 needed off 30 balls.
However, a couple a wickets could tighten things up.
Afridi to Kohli, 1 run, a forward press and then a gentle nudge through mid-on.
Batting is so easy for this man and keeps strike .
Afridi to Dhoni, 1 run, too full and on the off stump, Dhoni drives it crisply along the ground to long-offThe crowd goes "Dhoni, Dhoni," as the Indian skipper gets ready to face .
Afridi to Kohli, 1 run, short enough for Kohli to rock back and punch to long-on .
Afridi to Kohli, no run, Kohli tries to run it down to third man, but the ball spins past the outside edge .
Afridi to Kohli, no run, flighted delivery just around the off stump line, Kohli watchfully defends .
Afridi to Kohli, FOUR, a wicket fell at the other end, but nothing stops Kohli from playing his shots!
What a shot that is.
Flighted very full from Afridi, Kohli drives through cover and beats the man inside the ring, sweeper cover had no chanceShahid Afridi [ .
is back into the attackMS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease .
Riaz to Yuvraj, out Caught by Sami!!
In the airrr, this is not going the distance.
There is a man stationed under it and the catch is taken.
The umpire has asked Yuvraj to wait to check for the no-ball, well, that was well inside the line.
Not sure why he even wanted to check that again.
So Pakistan have broken this dangerous looking 61-run partnership that was running away with the game.
Slower delivery short and outside off stump, maybe Yuvraj could have gone off-side, instead he opts to pull, gets the bottom of the bat and it goes straight to deep mid-wicket.
Yuvraj c Sami b Riaz  .
s-1]Riaz to Yuvraj, THAT'S OUT!!
Caught!!
Riaz to Kohli, 1 run, he goes that so well!
Allows the ball to come, plays very close to the body and taps it fine for the ball to run towards third man .
Riaz to Yuvraj, 1 run, pace off the ball and a sensible Yuvraj Singh just opens the face of the bat and guides it through backward point .
Riaz to Kohli, 1 run, slower delivery outside off stump, Kohli dabs it to third manThe crowd is very loud now and right behind the Indian team .
Riaz to Yuvraj, 1 run, Yuvraj is swinging his bat at it now!
Backs away but the bowler follows him with a shortish delivery, Yuvraj gets a thick outside edge that falls short of Irfan at third man .
Riaz to Yuvraj, SIX, Yuvraj Singh joins the party and look at the roar from the capacity Eden Gardens crowd.
Short delivery just outside off stump, not that high enough to trouble the batsman, Yuvraj rocks back and muscles the pull shot for a flat six over mid-wicketKohli is playing a blinder of an innings.
Shoaib Malik to Kohli, no run, Kohli tries to run it fine to third man, but picks out the man inside the ring .
Shoaib Malik to Kohli, FOUR, lovely hit to bring up the fifty partnership.
Flighted delivery on the stumps, Kohli sweeps and sweeps very hard, sends it along the ground and there was no one in the deep .
Shoaib Malik to Kohli, no run, Kohli pushes this towards mid-wicket .
Shoaib Malik to Kohli, SIX, top-edgeeeeee and shouts of "catch itttttttt," from the keeper.
Has he holed out?
Oh my word!
This has gone all the way?
So cruel for the bowler.
He's actually foxed the batsman a bit, yet six runs go against his name.
How good is that bat in Kohli's hand and how thick is that side?
Flighted delivery on the stumps, Kohli goes for the slog-sweep, went hard and that meant there was more speed on the ball and the extra legs to clear the fielder at deep backward square leg .
Shoaib Malik to Yuvraj, 1 run, flighted delivery on the stumps, Yuvraj sweeps to deep mid-wicket .
Shoaib Malik to Kohli, 1 run, Kohli uses his feet and carefully works this flighted delivery to deep square leg .
Shoaib Malik to Yuvraj, 2 wides, poor from Shoaib Malik.
Sprays the flighted delivery down the leg-side, Yuvraj tries to sweep fine, misses and the keeper can't collect cleanly, they get an extra run as well10 overs done.
India need 59 off 48 balls.
Kohli and Yuvraj have settled things after that double-blow from Sami.
Riaz to Kohli, no run, oh a soft leading edge and Kohli is lucky that it didn't carry to the bowler.
Short of a length delivery on the stumps, Kohli tries to work it on the on-side, closes the bat face a little early and gets the edge .
Riaz to Yuvraj, 1 run, bad shot I would say because that was ball way outside off stump to be playing the pull shot.
Better of attempting the slap or cut.
Yuvraj toe-ends it through the vacant mid-on region .
Riaz to Yuvraj, no run, back of a length on the off stump, Yuvraj defends towards short cover and sets off, Kohli quickly yells and stops Yuvraj.
A run was never on there .
Riaz to Yuvraj, no run, the slower ball outside off stump, Yuvraj tries to run it down to third man, but only connects with thin air .
Riaz to Kohli, 1 run, don't give him width outside off stump, he'll keeping guiding and steering for ones and twos towards third man.
So easily done by Kohli .
Riaz to Kohli, FOUR, in the airrrr, not controlled at all!
Could have gone to hand, instead he picks up a boundary.
Skipper Afridi is not happy with Sharjeel Khan, who makes a mess at the rope.

Shortish in length, Kohli played a half-hearted pull, put it to the right of mid-wicket, Sharjeel got there and put in the slide, but couldn't flick it back properlyWahab Riaz, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack .
Shoaib Malik to Yuvraj, 2 runs, Yuvraj flicks uppishly, mid-wicket is empty and a smart Kohli pushes his partner through for the second run .
Shoaib Malik to Yuvraj, no run, half-shout for LBW as Yuvraj misses the sweep and gets hit on the body, hit him on the chest and was easily bouncing over the sticks.
The sweep is going to be a dangerous shot to play unless it's very full because of the turn and bounce on offer on this surface .
Shoaib Malik to Yuvraj, 2 runs, that's played away nicely by Yuvraj.
Flighted delivery on the stumps, Yuvraj gets down on knee and sweeps fine past short fine legNow there is a man at slip for Yuvi.
Shoaib Malik to Kohli, 1 run, flighted delivery on the stumps, Kohli flicks it to deep mid-wicket and brings up India's fifty .
Shoaib Malik to Kohli, wide, spinning down the leg-side, Kohli lets it go .
Shoaib Malik to Yuvraj, 1 run, and the trouble starts straightaway!
It's so surprising to see Afridi not having a slip!
Yuvi would have been out if there was one!
Pitches on off and turns square, foxes Yuvraj on the defence, bounces extra and takes the glove en route to short third manInteresting to see no slip being employed for Yuvraj.

Shoaib Malik to Kohli, 1 run, to keep the LBW in play, Malik bowls from round the wicket to Kohli, but bowls too full and gets clipped along the ground to deep mid-wicketShoaib Malik, right-arm off break, comes into the attackMailk comes on.
Kohli won't mind because the ball will be spinning into him.
However, life will be difficult for Yuvraj, for he's a left-hander.
Afridi to Kohli, 1 run, flighted delivery on the stumps, Kohli leans forward and drives along the ground to long-off and keeps strike .
Afridi to Yuvraj, 1 run, down the leg-side, easily tickled to fine leg, Kohli asks his partner if he wants two as fine leg had a bit of ground to cover to his left, but Yuvraj is happy with one .
Afridi to Kohli, 1 run, oh that wasn't convincing from Afridi.

The quicker delivery from Afridi, Kohli was on the back foot, it came quickly onto him and he almost took this off the off stump, tapped it through cover-pointAfridi is bowling over wicket to Kohli and round the wicket for Yuvraj .
Afridi to Yuvraj, 1 run, very full delivery on the stumps, Yuvraj sweeps well but long leg tidies up .

Afridi to Kohli, 1 run, "two, two," said Kohli as soon as he drove this flighted delivery crisply off the front foot and wide of long-off, but changes his mind, Yuvraj was halfway down the pitch for the second run, but had enough time to get backAfridi v Kohli is going to be interesting with the ball turning square .
Afridi to Yuvraj, 1 run, flighted delivery on the off stump, Yuvraj wrists it with the spin to long-onSo that 12-run over has settled things a bit for India.
Sami to Kohli, no run, fullish and outside off stump, Kohli drives it to cover .
Sami to Kohli, 2 runs, slower delivery on the off stump, Kohli works it off the inside half of the bat to backward square leg, calls for two and comes back in time.
The throw was wide of the keeper as well .
Sami to Yuvraj, 1 run, where is mid-wicket, Shahid Afridi?
It would have been a dolly.
Knowing Yuvraj's struggle against the short ball, Sami bangs it into the pitch, Yuvraj tries the pull, but splices it, mid-on had too much ground to cover and was never going to get there .
Sami to Yuvraj, FOUR, maybe this is why Yuvraj Singh wanted the strike and denied that second run.
Lovely cover-drive.
Looks so good when he gets going.
Full and slanted across outside off stump, Yuvraj, with his big bat lift, nails the drive to perfection and even a full length dive to his left from Amir wasn't good enough .
Sami to Kohli, 1 run, slower delivery on the stumps, Kohli works it to deep square leg, wants two but Yuvraj says no .
Sami to Kohli, FOUR, wow!
Good shot!
The crowd gets going with that hit from India's No.3.
Short of a length delivery wide outside off stump, Kohli allows the ball to come and punches it with an angled bat, beats both backward point and third man.
So just like his first over, Sami concedes a boundary first ball .
Afridi to Yuvraj, no run, a short leg would have swallowed that.
Flighted delivery on the stumps, Yuvraj leans forward to defend, gets an inside edge onto pad, lobs in the air but falls safely .

Afridi to Yuvraj, wide, Afridi darts this in and also gets it to grip, too good for Yuvraj, but it went down the leg-side, another good take by the keeper as he was blinded by the batsman for a while .
Afridi to Yuvraj, no run, waits for the ball to come back in and watchfully works it into the on-side .
Afridi to Yuvraj, no run, flighted delivery on the stumps, turned into the on-side .
Afridi to Yuvraj, wide, oh big turn and the keeper did really well to collect and save a few extra runs.
Spinning down the leg-side, Sarfraz moves to his right and goes well .
Afridi to Kohli, 1 run, once again Kohli plays early.
Shortish and spinning away outside off stump, Kohli wanted to cut, the ball went off the inside half of the bat .
Afridi to Yuvraj, 1 run, round the wicket, on the leg stump, Yuvraj glances this to fine leg .
Afridi to Kohli, 1 run, shortish and spinning away outside off stump, Kohli goes early into the pull, under-edges it through backward square leg.
Kohli went so deep in the crease that he almost stepped onto the stumpsShahid Afridi, right-arm leg break, comes into the attackWow!
What a turnaround for Sami.
Thrashed for four first ball and then oversteps to concede a free-hit, but he got two-in-two.
Mind you, he was drafted into the side for this game at the expense of Imad Wasim and Sami has justified the selection.
Sami to Yuvraj, no run, cross-seamed length delivery close to the off stump, Yuvraj manages to defend .
Sami to Yuvraj, no run, the hat-trick ball is negotiated.
Short of a length delivery on the stumps, Yuvraj was late on the defence, gets hit high on the thigh padYuvraj Singh, left handed bat, comes to the crease .
Sami to Raina, out Bowled!!
And there goes the leg-stump cartwheeling towards the keeper.
Sami is on a hat-trick.
Stunned faces in the crowd.
Raina can't believe that he's been dismissed.
It all happened so quickly for him.
Why on earth would you hop everytime on the crease when a pacy bowler is bowling short of length close to your body?
Raina awkwardly tries to defend and drags it back onto the stumps.
Raina b Sami  .
)Sami to Raina, THAT'S OUT!!
Bowled!
!Suresh Raina, left handed bat, comes to the crease .
Sami to Dhawan, out Bowled!!
How quickly does fortune change?
Sami was struggling to get things right and all of a sudden, he roars in delight after castling the batsman.

Short of a length delivery on the off stump, we all know that Dhawan is a lazy front foot mover, just tries to defend with soft hands and probably wanting to run it to third man, ends up playing it onto the stumps off the face of the bat.
Yes, you got to play with soft hands, but not with such soft hands.
A bit more hard hands would have meant that it would have been a proper defence.
Dhawan b Sami  .
5) [4s-1]Sami to Dhawan, THAT'S OUT!!
Bowled!!
Sami to Dhawan, no run, Dhawan fails to make use of the free-hit!
Sami gets away with a poor delivery.
Once again short wide is this slower delivery, Dhawan backs away slightly and cuts hard, only manages to get the bottom of the bat onto it and straight to backward point .
Sami to Dhawan, no ball, oh no!
What have you done Sami?
He's overstepped the line and it's going to be a free-hit.
Slower delivery slanted across, swing and a miss .
Sami to Dhawan, FOUR, Dhawan gets it in the gap and improves his strike-rate.
Sami starts with a slower delivery first up, but he gave a lot of width for Dhawan to play with.
Mind you, Dhawan is very good square on the off-side and he generally won't miss out on an opportunity.
This was the square drive timed sweetly between backward point and the diving cover-pointMohammad Sami, right-arm fast, comes into the attackJust 2 off that over.
Dhawan is struggling for timing.
Now what that does is it puts extra pressure on Kohli.
Interesting times ahead!
Irfan to Kohli, no run, the off-cutting slower delivery outside off stump and Kohli had no clue about it.
However, he did well to drop his hands and let the ball go though after being out-thought by the bowler.
The length was shortish from Irfan and that gave Kohli the time to make a last minute change .
Irfan to Dhawan, 1 run, good length delivery on the stumps, Dhawan swings across the line, the ball takes the inside half of the bat and goes on the bounce towards deep square leg .
Irfan to Dhawan, no run, another dot ball.
Pressure builds on Dhawan and he desperately wants to get off strike.
Can't hit the ball straight to hand and expect your partner to respond though.
Once again Kohli rightly shouts loud and asks Dhawan to stay at his end.
This was mistimed towards cover-point againDhawan has scored just 1 run off 9 balls now.
Irfan to Dhawan, no run, short of length delivery outside off stump, Dhawan goes for the cut, but the slow pitch meant he played a little early and toe-ended it to cover-point .
Irfan to Dhawan, no run, Dhawan defends this length ball towards short cover and looks for a non-existent run, but Kohli yells and stops him .
Irfan to Kohli, 1 run, slower delivery on the leg stump, Kohli works it to fine leg and opens his accountAmir has bowled two lovely overs.
Time for Irfan to step up.
His first over was very poor.
Can he do justice this time around?
We'll wait and watch.
Amir to Dhawan, no run, once again Dhawan is hit on the thigh pad, short of length delivery angled in at  .
kph, Dhawan is late in bringing his bat down, but luckily it was going down leg and also bouncing over .
Amir to Dhawan, no run, short of length once again, the cutter from the left-armer, Dhawan hangs back and defends .
Amir to Dhawan, no run, full delivery outside off stump, Dhawan drives and finds the man at cover .
Amir to Dhawan, no run, the slower delivery from Amir, the ball came back just a bit and also bounced extra, Dhawan was beaten on the defence and hit him high on the thigh pad.
Half-shout for LBW from Pakistan .

Amir to Dhawan, leg byes, 2 runs, short of length delivery down the leg-side, Dhawan misses the tickle, ball rolls towards fine leg off the thigh padVirat Kohli, right handed bat, comes to the crease .
Amir to Rohit, out Caught by Shoaib Malik!!
It's high in the airrrrrrr.
Who wants it?
A couple of fielders are very close but Malik holds on.
Excellent catch.
Afridi came from mid-off, but Malik called for it rushing from extra-cover and took it cleanly.
A bad stroke attempted by Rohit Sharma.
Good length delivery on the off stump, this is not a pitch to be playing the on the rise hinted Sunil Gavaskar on air in the last over and Rohit pays the price.
Just goes for the lofted drive over mid-off, but the ball hit the bottom of the bat and went very high.
The fielder did the rest.
Pakistan get the early breakthrough they were looking for.
Rohit c Shoaib Malik b Amir  .
1) [4s-2]Amir to Rohit, THAT'S OUT!!
Caught!!
Irfan to Rohit, 1 run, short of length delivery on the leg stump, Rohit glances it to fine leg .
Irfan to Rohit, FOUR, the slower ball attempted but it's way too short, Rohit swivels and pulls fine through the vacant backward square leg region.
Second boundary of the over for India .
Irfan to Rohit, no run, uppish, but safe!
Poor shot from Rohit.
It appeared as if he made up his mind at the last moment to attempt the on-the-rise drive.
Short of a length and climbing high, Rohit splices the shot to mid-off .
Irfan to Rohit, no run, cracking back foot punch and a brilliant piece of fielding there at backward point by Ahmed Shehzad.
Short of a length delivery just outside off stump, Rohit plays the shot on one leg, Shehzad flies to his right and saves a certain boundary .
Irfan to Rohit, no run, much better from Irfan, keep it on a good length outside off stump, Rohit shoulders arms, good bounce for Irfan on that occasion .
Irfan to Rohit, wide, Irfan goes round the wicket, but gets the radar wrong, bangs this short and it goes down the leg-side, Rohit tries to help it on its way but misses .
Irfan to Rohit, FOUR, poor start from Irfan.
The new ball will be the best time to bat and India would want to make full use of the overs, Irfan has to understand that and bowl well.
A dreadful ball first up in a big game.

Short and angled across outside off stump, Rohit cuts deliberately over cover-point and picks up an easy boundaryMohammad Irfan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attackSo a quiet start for both sides.
Amir did not swing and India did not get freebies.
Amir to Dhawan, no run, beaten!
kph on this full delivery outside off stump, Dhawan plays a loose drive and gets beaten .
Amir to Rohit, 1 run, with the left-armer's angle from over the wicket, Rohit uses the width on this good length delivery and runs it down to third man .
Amir to Dhawan, 1 run, no swing on this one too.

Pacy full delivery, but the line is wrong and down the leg-side, Dhawan clips it away nicely with a strong bottom hand grip, fine leg runs to his right and tidies upDhawan not happy with movement behind the bowler's arm.
Sorted now and we are good to carry on.
Wide slip in place .
Amir to Rohit, leg byes, 1 run, leg-stumpish from Amir, Rohit wanted to tickle it fine, but failed to connect and the short of length delivery rolled behind square off the thigh pad .
Amir to Rohit, wide, Amir sprays this wide outside off stump, Rohit lets it go and an easy call for the umpire.
First runs for India .
Amir to Rohit, no run, this is slightly tailing back into the right-hander, Rohit tucks this into the on-side .
Amir to Rohit, no run, beaten straightaway!
The interesting thing was that the ball didn't swing.
Just a full delivery angled across the right-hander, Rohit hung his bat away from the body as he tried to defend, the ball missed the outside edgeRohit and Dhawan are at the crease.
Rohit is on strike.
Amir will open the attackWelcome back for the chase.
The players are out in the middle.
Amir to open the bowling.
Can he produce something similar to what he did in the Asia Cup?Malik: "Well it was tough, but I scored some runs for my side which is a great sign.
We have something to defend, pitch is not easy to score freely.
If we score  .
, we can give a tough time to the Indians.
It is not easy to play the big shots, place your shots in the gaps for singles and doubles and score off the bad ball.
Honestly no (when asked if he was surprised with the amount of spin the pitch took), even the first match against Bangladesh was turning, but not as this much.
It is not the curator's fault, it is the weather's and it is not in your control.
It is not going to be easy to chase this total.
"There's no doubt both teams have erred in reading this pitch.
India didn't play the extra spinner.
Also, for once, Dhoni's use of part-timers was questionable.
Surely he underbowled them.
That point is only vindicated on having a glance at Bumrah's and Pandya's figures.
Meanwhile, Pakistan have four seamers in their artillery.
FOUR seamers on a spin paradise.
Will it cost them?It's not often that we get to use common sense and a Pakistani batting lineup in the same sentence.
But they showed good application at the top (except Sharjeel).
Focus was to build along steadily and not aiming too high which can be a trap.
The run rate meandered along and wasn't great but they didn't panic.
Afridi promoted himself, played a labourous 14-ball 8.
They didn't panic.
Then Malik came along and showed his class being the protagonist of a 41-run partnership (off 24 balls) with Umar Akmal.Pakistan have put up a very competitive score on this monster of a pitch.
Such a priceless partnership between Shoaib Malik and Umar Akmal, coming at a rapid rate given how difficult it is to bat out there.
The sinister nature of this track became pretty apparent when Ashwin turned it square with the new ball.
Huge huge turn, the kind which renders the skill level of a batsman irrelevant and shoves the game to a no-contest.
All bets off.
Real shame after all the grandiloquence of the buildup.
Anyway, let's not allow the curator to steal the spotlight.I don't want to sound pedantic here.
But let me reiterate - this isn't a T20I pitch.
Not even an ODI pitch for that matter.
How can you expect a decent contest between bat and ball when the ball is turning six inches and we don't even have a ripping spinner like a Shane Warne or a Murali on display.
Heard on air that Sourav Ganguly too was surprised as to how the pitch has behaved today.
But a very poor advertisement for cricket and it is happening in a WT20 game between India and Pakistan.
Such a high-profile game, spoiled and at the mercy of a dubious pitch.
Let's see what the pitch-happy ICC has to say about this track!
With that I rest my case and give my bleeding fingers a well-deserved rest .

World T20, it doesn't get any better than this, it is India up against Pakistan, a match which brings the economies of two countries to a grinding halt.Preview by Prakash Govindasreenivasan: 

The uncertainty is over, the security is in place and the focus is squarely on the cricket to follow.
The dust has truly settled as India and Pakistan gear up to take on each other in yet another high-stakes World Cup clash at the Eden Gardens on Saturday (March 19).
The stakes this time, however, will be a lot higher than expected.
The contrasting starts to their respective World T20 campaigns is bound to have a major repercussion when the two take on each other.
For India, beyond the bragging rights in such big tournaments, a win will be key to keep their campaign alive.
A heavy defeat in the low-scorer against New Zealand gave them a Net Run Rate (NRR) of - .
If by the end of the Super 10 stage, three teams in the group are tied on points, NRR will have a say in the fate of these sides.

For Pakistan, a win would snap their unending misery against their rivals in World Cups but the bigger picture will be the fact that they would've secured two wins against the two Asian sides of their group and will proceed with an added advantage when they face New Zealand and Australia, both in Mohali.
Form-wise, Shahid Afridi's men will need to carry a deep sense of self-belief that they are finally primed to break the elusive duck against their nemesis.
India, on the other hand, have a lot to ponder over.

While Ravichandran Ashwin preferred to brush aside the defeat to New Zealand as a bad day in office, India desperately need to recoup their A game that helped them become Asia Cup champions less than a month ago.
Even in that tournament, the Indian batters, barring Virat Kohli, struggled to cope with the excessive pace of Mohammad Amir.
Even on a slow burner at Eden, Amir, as evidenced in his performance against Afghanistan, could crank up the pace.
When: India vs Pakistan, 19 March, Group B -  .

0 PM IST

Where: Eden Gardens, Kolkata

What to expect: Kolkata is expected to be very warm, humid and partly cloudy on Saturday, with a minimum temperature of 26 degree Celsius.
The wicket was a little on the slower side in the night game between Sri Lanka and Afghanistan but suited the batsmen a lot more.
The wickets also aren't too generous towards spinners, like the Nagpur wicket, narrowing the tussle down to pure skill in the spin departments on either side.

Team News:

India

While pressure is a given in such encounters, Ashwin carried a sense of nonchalance into the pre-match press conference, stressing on the fact that the players are now used to such high-octane games.
In practice, the most notable sight was of Mohammed Shami steaming in and beating Virat Kohli's bat with pace on several occasions.
Shami was one of the best bowlers at the  .
World Cup but has since spent more time on the doctor's table than at the pitch.
An injury setback, a surgery and months of layoff later, the 26-year-old seems to be back to his original self.
It will be interesting to see if Dhoni is tempted to draft Shami in for the marquee clash.

Pakistan

Barring any late, freak injuries or illnesses, Pakistan are unlikely to tamper with a winning combination.
Ahmed Shehzad's excellent start to the tournament has given the team management a reason to revel in their decision to make a last-minute change to the squad.
Mohammad Hafeez and Shoaib Malik have also been in the runs in the two games (including warm-up against Sri Lanka), with Umar Akmal yet to get a real shot at taking his Asia Cup T20 form forward.
Among the bowlers, Imad Wasim's role could be crucial, given India's recent struggle against spin.
The Who's Who in attendance: An India-Pakistan encounter is never short of being a carnival.
On Saturday, Eden Gardens will be graced by the presence of some of the best cricketers of yesteryears from either side of the border.
Four World Cup winners - Imran Khan, Sachin Tendulkar, Sunil Gavaskar and Virender Sehwag - will add to the sheen of the highly-anticipated contest.
Amitabh Bachchan, one of the biggest Bollywood actors in India, and Shafqat Amanat Ali Khan, a Pakistani classical singer, will render their voices for the two national anthems.
